# Airgead Banking Project

## Project Summary
The Airgead Banking App helps users visualize how their investments grow over time, teaching students important lessons about fiscal responsibility and compound interest. The program calculates year-end balances with and without monthly deposits based on user input.

## What I Did Well
I organized the project using object-oriented programming, keeping the investment logic inside a dedicated class, and ensured strong input validation to make the app stable and user-friendly.

## Where I Could Improve
One area for improvement would be to separate user input/output from the calculation logic to enhance modularity. Adding the option to save results to a file would also make the application more flexible and user-focused.

## Most Challenging Part
The most challenging part was accurately calculating monthly compound interest. I overcame it by researching financial formulas and carefully testing the calculations. I am adding more finance resources and C++ best-practice references to my support network.

## Transferable Skills
Through this project, I strengthened important skills such as object-oriented design, input validation, financial calculation handling, and writing modular, maintainable code, all of which are highly transferable to future coursework and professional software development.

## Readability and Maintainability
To keep the program readable and adaptable, I used clear naming conventions, consistent formatting, detailed comments, and structured, focused functions.
